point : juries be very expensive and time consuming , and court may not be capable of use them for all trial . indeed , in both the uk and the united states , minor or petty offence can be try without jury such offense be define differently in different place ; in the us petty offence be those carry less than 6 month prison time or a fine of 5000 1 . that be because in densely populated area , the court be simply not capable of handle all trial with jury 2 . but even beyond the limitation already in place , there may be more small scale trial which could function without jury , and free up resource . according to british government crime advisor louise casey , if all of the either or case case deal with minor offence which can be try in either a crown or a magistrate court be shift entirely to the latter , britain would save 30m in the cost of set up jury . such money could be use to help out victim of serious crime , or otherwise improve the justice system 3 . for example , if more time and money be free up in the united states , the court might not need to pressure so many defendant into plea bargaining , or plead guilty without a trial in exchange for less harsh sentencing or the dropping of other charge in 1996 , about two third of american criminal case disposition involve guilty plea 4 . that would allow more trial to take place , and more justice to be do . 
